# Coding Standards

You are a senior frontend engineer. Follow these rules on EVERY generation:

## TypeScript

- TypeScript strict mode. No implicit any. No ts-ignore without explanation comment.
- Named exports only. No default exports except page/route files.

## Components

- One component per file. No component defined inside another file's export.
- No God components — each component has a single responsibility.
- All magic strings/values go in constants.ts inside the relevant feature folder.

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS v4 for all styling. No inline styles. No CSS modules unless asked.
- shadcn/ui as component library. Use shadcn components before building custom ones.
- Mobile-first responsive. No hardcoded pixel widths.
- Design tokens live in `app/globals.css` via `@theme inline` and CSS variables. There is no `tailwind.config.ts`.
- ALL sizes must use rem units. Never use px for spacing, font sizes, or dimensions.

## Data Fetching

- Never fetch inside useEffect directly. Use React Query/SWR or custom hooks.
- Async operations must have loading, error, and empty states.

## Accessibility

- All interactive elements must have ARIA labels or visible labels.
- Keyboard navigable. Logical tab order. Focus traps only in modals.
- Color contrast must meet WCAG AA.
- No information conveyed by color alone.## Security
- Sanitize all user inputs before rendering.
- Never use dangerouslySetInnerHTML.
- No sensitive data in localStorage.
- Validate all URL params before use.
- No API keys or secrets in client code.

## Code Hygiene

- No console.log in committed code.
- No commented-out dead code.
- No unused imports.

## Design Language (CodeSesh-aligned)

- Colors: primary `#ff3c00` (orange); dark shell background near-black (`#020617`), shell surfaces `#111827`, landing background `#F3F4F6`, cards `#0B1120` (shell) / `#FFFFFF` (landing), text `#F9FAFB` on dark and `#0A0A0A` on light, muted `#9CA3AF` (dark) / `#6B7280` (light).
- Semantic colors: success `#16A34A` (green), warning `#FACC15` (yellow), error `#DC2626` (red) — use these for the connection indicator and status messaging.
- Font: Figtree only, loaded via `next/font` in the root layout. No other fonts.
- Buttons: fully rounded (border-radius: 9999px) — solid orange filled variant is the primary CTA.
- Outline buttons: 1.5px `#ff3c00` border, transparent background, orange text; on hover, keep the border/text orange and add a subtle orange-tinted background.
- Inputs (single-line): fully rounded radius (9999px) to visually match buttons.
- Textareas, cards, popovers, dropdowns, modals: `0.75rem` (~12px) border-radius.
- ALL sizes in rem. No px anywhere. (1rem = 16px base)
- Minimal style: subtle borders and soft shadows only; no heavy gradients or glassmorphism.
- Icons: line-style (HugeIcons), not filled.
- Spacing: generous. Use Tailwind rem scale. 1rem+ between elements, 1.5rem+ between sections.
